      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly draining to feel like you are living a performance when your true self feels lost, and your exhaustion is completely valid. You do not have to pretend or force yourself to be someone you are no longer; it is okay to stop performing and simply exist as you are right now. If the effort to maintain a false version of yourself feels too heavy, it is perfectly reasonable to rest, step away, and let yourself be exactly as you are without any expectation of fixing the past.",
      "source": "target",
